   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Ok Mobis dying enables Trug to crush everything immediately when he comes into play. (Should you need to do that)<br>
<br>
Point of the deck? Murdering everything in play...often.<br>
<br>
Rayalons to recycle the shock waves and cataclysms<br>
Furok Guardians to recycle the creatures that recycle the spells<br>
<br>
Robe of the ages because you&#39;ll be playing an ass-load of spells<br>
<br>
Sandswirl because I&#39;m addicted to it and have to have it in everydeck. That and it takes care of nasty creature abilities. (I never plan on using for more then a round...I suppose Feet O&#39; stone would work too)<br>
<br>
Ormagons...self explanitory.<br>
<br>
Maelstrom flasks and Cataclysms give you a nice (and cheap) way to clear the board. You&#39;ll be cycling through your deck pretty  fast and often so who cares what you lose!<br>
<br>
This deck is really fun to play in team games...that is if you don&#39;t mind getting hit alot =) </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
